  "prompt": "3 block with mas 6kg,9kg,10kg are connected as shown.The coefficient of friction between the table & 10kg block is 0.20.find; acceleration of system?",
  "response": "To find the acceleration of the system, we need to analyze the forces acting on each block and apply Newton's second law. Let's assume the system is set up as follows:\n\n- Two blocks of masses \\(6 \\text{ kg}\\) and \\(9 \\text{ kg}\\) are hanging freely, connected by strings over a pulley, while a third block of mass \\(10 \\text{ kg}\\) is on a table with friction.\n\n### Step 1: Identify the forces\n1. **For the \\(6 \\text{ kg}\\) and \\(9 \\text{ kg}\\) blocks**: The force due to gravity is \\(F = mg\\).\n   - For the \\(6 \\text{ kg}\\) block: \\(F_1 = 6 \\times 9.8 = 58.8 \\text{ N}\\) (downward).\n   - For the \\(9 \\text{ kg}\\) block: \\(F_2 = 9 \\times 9.8 = 88.2 \\text{ N}\\) (downward).\n\n2. **For the \\(10 \\text{ kg}\\) block**:\n   - The normal force \\(N = mg = 10 \\times 9.8 = 98 \\text{ N}\\).\n   - The frictional force \\(f = \\mu N = 0.20 \\times 98 = 19.6 \\text{ N}\\) (opposing motion).\n\n### Step 2: Write the equations of motion\nLet\u2019s assume the \\(9 \\text{ kg}\\) block accelerates downward, causing the \\(6 \\text{ kg}\\) and \\(10 \\text{ kg}\\) blocks to accelerate to the right.\n\n- For the \\(6 \\text{ kg}\\) block (tension \\(T_1\\)):  \n  \\(T_1 - 58.8 = 6a\\)\n\n- For the \\(9 \\text{ kg}\\) block (tension \\(T_2\\)):  \n  \\(88.2 - T_2 = 9a\\)\n\n- For the \\(10 \\text{ kg}\\) block:  \n  \\(T_2 - T_1 - 19.6 = 10a\\)\n\n### Step 3: Solve the equations\nFrom the \\(6 \\text{ kg}\\) and \\(9 \\text{ kg}\\) block equations:\n\\[\nT_1 = 58.8 + 6a \\quad \\text{and} \\quad T_2 = 88.2 - 9a\n\\]\n\nSubstitute \\(T_1\\) and \\(T_2\\) into the \\(10 \\text{ kg}\\) block equation:\n\\[\n(88.2 - 9a) - (58.8 + 6a) - 19.6 = 10a\n\\]\n\\[\n88.2 - 9a - 58.8 - 6a - 19.6 = 10a\n\\]\n\\[\n9.8 - 15a = 10a\n\\]\n\\[\n9.8 = 25a\n\\]\n\\[\na = \\frac{9.8}{25} = 0.392 \\, \\text{m/s}^2\n\\]\n\n### Final Answer:\nThe acceleration of the system is **\\(0.392 \\, \\text{m/s}^2\\)**.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
